Class WatchableRef<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • akka.typed.internal.WatchableRef<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ActorRef<T>, ActorRefImpl<T>, java.lang.Comparable<ActorRef<?>>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FunctionRef, FutureRef

    public abstract class WatchableRef<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ActorRef<T>, ActorRefImpl<T>
    The mechanics for synthetic ActorRefs that have a lifecycle and support being watched.

      • path

        public ActorPath path()
        Description copied from interface: ActorRef
        The hierarchical path name of the referenced Actor. The lifecycle of the ActorRef is fully contained within the lifecycle of the ActorPath and more than one Actor instance can exist with the same path at different points in time, but not concurrently.
        Specified by:
        path in interface ActorRef<T>

        protected abstract void terminate()
        Callback that is invoked when this ref has terminated. Even if doTerminate() is called multiple times, this callback is invoked only once.
